rising in value (nov 2013). cheat sheet 10 jiao is 1 yuan (元), the base unit yuan is commonly called kuai (块) jiao is commonly called mao (毛) 10 is shí (十) 100 is bǎi (百) 1000 is qiān (千) 10000 is wàn (万) the official subdivisions of the yuan are the jiao (角), at 10 jiao to the yuan, and the fen (分) at 10 fen to the jiao. the fen is essentially extinct nowadays but may still be seen in less developed areas. a coin worth ¥0.10 will thus say 壹角 ("1 jiao"), not "10 fen", on it. 